Preconditions:
The input array `nums` must not be null.
The input array `nums` must have at least two elements.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the length of the longest harmonious subsequence.
The returned length should be greater than or equal to zero.
The returned length should be less than or equal to the length of the input array `nums`.
The method should handle cases where there is no harmonious subsequence by returning zero.
The method should handle cases where there are multiple harmonious subsequences by returning the length of the longest one.